            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I feared that it would wind up being a cheap approximation of survival horror with a heavy veneer of fan service and sadly, I was right. Between the air-headed characters, woeful dialogue and lackluster combat, it was really hard to find something to enjoy about ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Red Colony",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". Even the most die hard fans of survival horror and anime games should steer clear: there are much better options available on the eShop for both genres. This game is a lot like a faulty desk you buy and have to put together yourself: you’ve got all the right pieces, but they don’t seem to fit together properly and the desk still wobbles once you’re done.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
